to increase.

244
00:12:19,559 --> 00:12:21,279
So tonight,
we thought we'd try and explain

245
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:24,279
exactly why Bad Bunny tickets
are so expensive,

246
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:27,240
who is making money off them, and
what you might be able to do about it

247
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:29,960
that does not involve
selling your husband's feet.

248
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:33,639
And let's start with the company
that you're immediately thinking of:

249
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:34,840
Ticketmaster.

250
00:12:34,919 --> 00:12:38,120
They are the biggest player
in the ticket market, by far,

251
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:40,559
and claim they strive
to put fans first,

252
00:12:40,639 --> 00:12:43,440
and that "the people
we care most about are the fans."

253
00:12:43,879 --> 00:12:47,120
And yet, as anyone who has ever
bought a ticket from them knows,

254
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:50,039
that's generally not the feeling
you get when dealing with them,

255
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:51,600
as this YouTuber explains.

256
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:55,039
If there was anything
that I had as a wish,

257
00:12:55,120 --> 00:12:57,440
for any big artist
or band that comes through,

258
00:12:57,519 --> 00:13:00,399
whether it's K-pop,
whether it's a western artist,

259
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:02,480
I don't give a shit
if you're a magician,

260
00:13:02,559 --> 00:13:06,360
any big ticket person that ever
comes through and does a concert,

261
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:08,159
never use Ticketmaster.

262
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:11,919
